281
00:14:07,030 --> 00:14:08,010
-It really hurts.
-Hong Hui.

282
00:14:08,100 --> 00:14:09,310
Answer my question first.

283
00:14:10,070 --> 00:14:11,440
In this pitch darkness,

284
00:14:11,830 --> 00:14:13,340
what were you sneaking around for?

285
00:14:13,990 --> 00:14:14,750
I...

286
00:14:14,770 --> 00:14:16,460
I was bored, so I just wanted to take a walk.

287
00:14:16,980 --> 00:14:18,280
-You...
-No.

288
00:14:18,320 --> 00:14:20,360
You need to come up with a different excuse.

289
00:14:22,730 --> 00:14:23,710
I don't have any other excuse.

290
00:14:23,790 --> 00:14:24,570
I'm dizzy from the fall.

291
00:14:24,630 --> 00:14:25,560
The fall has messed up my brain.

292
00:14:25,560 --> 00:14:26,510
I can't come up with anything.

293
00:14:35,020 --> 00:14:35,670
You...

294
00:14:36,010 --> 00:14:37,520
Gao Yin, look at him.

295
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:38,870
He's not dead from the fall, is he?

296
00:14:39,020 --> 00:14:40,150
Can you check on him for me?

297
00:14:40,150 --> 00:14:42,160
It's just a face-plant.

298
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:43,750
At most, it's embarrassing.

299
00:14:43,890 --> 00:14:45,190
Embarrassing to death.

300
00:14:47,710 --> 00:14:48,670
Is he dead?

301
00:14:48,840 --> 00:14:50,710
He didn't die of embarrassment, did he?

302
00:14:51,250 --> 00:14:52,510
Can you check for me?

303
00:14:52,710 --> 00:14:54,760
He's dead? Embarrassed to death?

304
00:14:55,690 --> 00:14:57,630
Died of embarrassment?

305
00:15:02,460 --> 00:15:03,390
I'm off.

306
00:15:04,280 --> 00:15:05,010
He...

307
00:15:07,750 --> 00:15:08,750
What does she mean?

308
00:15:11,360 --> 00:15:11,910
I'm off too.

309
00:15:12,270 --> 00:15:12,790
Wait.

310
00:15:13,310 --> 00:15:13,910
You...

311
00:15:15,440 --> 00:15:16,580
You just left like that.

312
00:15:26,630 --> 00:15:27,300
I...

313
00:15:27,950 --> 00:15:29,210
Don't hit me. I'm awake.

314
00:15:29,870 --> 00:15:30,820
Playing dead.

315
00:15:31,230 --> 00:15:33,310
Next time you play dead, I'll really beat you to death.

316
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:35,130
I'll see if you dare to play dead again.

317
00:15:35,160 --> 00:15:36,390
It hurts. It hurts so much.

318
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:37,790
Untie me. Untie me.

319
00:15:37,810 --> 00:15:38,740
Untie me. Untie me. Untie me.

320
00:15:39,690 --> 00:15:40,820
Play dead?

321
00:15:44,210 --> 00:15:45,550
I shouldn't have helped you up.

322
00:15:45,570 --> 00:15:47,170
Next time, I'll tie you up here for a day.

323
00:15:48,100 --> 00:15:49,310
There won't be a next time.

324
00:15:50,920 --> 00:15:51,920
Hong Hui!

325
00:15:51,980 --> 00:15:54,080
Next time, I'll set a trap at your doorstep.

326
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:55,670
You'll be caught as soon as you step out!

327
00:15:55,670 --> 00:15:56,840
You think I'm scared of you?

328
00:15:56,860 --> 00:15:57,800
-I'm off.
-Stop!

329
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:00,850
Damn Hong Hui.

330
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:04,110
You did a good job learning this dish today.

331
00:16:04,690 --> 00:16:05,670
However,

332
00:16:06,770 --> 00:16:10,310
being a mother shouldn't just be about cooking, right?

333
00:16:10,940 --> 00:16:13,030
What else should a mother know how to do?

334
00:16:13,220 --> 00:16:14,400
I don't know about that.

335
00:16:14,420 --> 00:16:15,570
I've never been a mother either.

336
00:16:15,980 --> 00:16:16,720
Okay.

337
00:16:16,740 --> 00:16:18,910
I'll learn to be a good mother.

338
00:16:19,910 --> 00:16:20,980
How do you plan to learn?

339
00:16:21,050 --> 00:16:23,350
All mothers are different.

340
00:16:24,130 --> 00:16:27,070
Then I'll learn from the best of every mother.

341
00:16:29,070 --> 00:16:30,090
You can do that?

342
00:16:38,220 --> 00:16:40,460
It's so comfortable living here.

343
00:16:40,880 --> 00:16:42,740
Look how big this bamboo forest is.

344
00:16:48,770 --> 00:16:49,670
Tell me.

345
00:16:50,580 --> 00:16:51,510
Will I

346
00:16:51,510 --> 00:16:52,950
be able to eat your cooking every day from now on?

347
00:16:53,460 --> 00:16:54,350
Of course.

348
00:16:56,280 --> 00:16:57,110
Then,

349
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,800
will your cooking keep getting better?

350
00:17:00,060 --> 00:17:01,180
Definitely.

351
00:17:02,870 --> 00:17:03,560
Great.

352
00:17:04,339 --> 00:17:06,119
I don't like cooking anyway.

353
00:17:06,369 --> 00:17:07,790
So you can do all the cooking.

354
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:13,960
It's so quiet tonight.

355
00:17:16,079 --> 00:17:17,280
It feels really comfortable.

356
00:17:21,480 --> 00:17:22,349
This is nice.

357
00:17:41,570 --> 00:17:43,080
You can even strum like this.

358
00:17:47,670 --> 00:17:49,010
You haven't drunk any wine yet.

359
00:17:50,050 --> 00:17:51,750
Why have you become even more sorrowful?

360
00:17:54,280 --> 00:17:57,800
Gallant deeds always get sent away by driving wind.

361
00:17:58,840 --> 00:18:04,050
With wrath I draw my sword and I look around, feeling completely at a loss.

362
00:18:05,550 --> 00:18:07,440
Qu Ping indulges himself on the river, only missing the wine.

363
00:18:08,130 --> 00:18:11,230
After a thousand cups of wine, there will be no more worries.

364
00:18:14,850 --> 00:18:15,670
Nice.

365
00:18:16,340 --> 00:18:18,410
Life is about knowing each other,

366
00:18:18,440 --> 00:18:20,710
and knowing each other is all about wine.

367
00:18:33,240 --> 00:18:36,390
You guys are so flirtatious.

368
00:18:37,130 --> 00:18:37,920
Hong Hui.

369
00:18:38,350 --> 00:18:39,600
Don't you dare be like them.

370
00:18:40,080 --> 00:18:42,390
Or I'll beat you to a pulp.

371
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:45,650
Suddenly I heard the roar of the lion from the east of the river,

372
00:18:45,670 --> 00:18:48,090
and I felt a chill coming out of my whole body.

373
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:50,190
You're teaching him bad things again.

374
00:18:50,210 --> 00:18:51,710
Zhang Fang, I'll teach you a lesson.

375
00:18:51,710 --> 00:18:53,040
-Suddenly I heard the roar of the lion from the east of the river...
-Come here.

376
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:54,430
And I felt a chill coming out of my whole body.

377
00:18:54,780 --> 00:18:56,270
-Stop!
-Don't. Don't.

378
00:18:56,270 --> 00:18:57,350
-Come here.
-Don't.

379
00:18:57,350 --> 00:18:58,030
Don't move.

380
00:18:59,180 --> 00:19:00,190
Pepper. Pepper.

381
00:19:00,690 --> 00:19:01,520
Stop messing around.

382
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:08,120
Come back.

383
00:19:08,170 --> 00:19:09,150
I'm doing this for you.

384
00:19:13,280 --> 00:19:14,280
Go ahead and keep making trouble.

385
00:19:19,750 --> 00:19:20,670
A chill comes out of my whole body.

386
00:19:20,670 --> 00:19:21,630
You better be careful.

387
00:19:28,150 --> 00:19:29,430
If you keep this up,

388
00:19:29,450 --> 00:19:31,430
you'll be feeling a chill coming out of your whole body too.

389
00:19:33,680 --> 00:19:35,110
What are they doing here?

390
00:19:35,380 --> 00:19:37,550
Could this family be suspicious in some way?

391
00:19:37,570 --> 00:19:39,190
It's probably Wang's stronghold for informants.

392
00:19:39,460 --> 00:19:40,670
We've failed in our duty again.

393
00:19:40,710 --> 00:19:41,710
We didn't notice at all.

394
00:19:41,730 --> 00:19:43,480
Let's send someone to monitor this family when we get back.

395
00:19:43,560 --> 00:19:45,310
Yesterday, at this doorway,

396
00:19:45,350 --> 00:19:46,710
I saw a mother and daughter playing.

397
00:19:46,730 --> 00:19:47,710
It's just

398
00:19:47,750 --> 00:19:49,360
I don't know when they'll come out today.

399
00:19:49,810 --> 00:19:51,710
Why are we standing here,

400
00:19:51,750 --> 00:19:52,910
sneaking around like this?

401
00:19:53,450 --> 00:19:54,640
How weird.

402
00:19:57,530 --> 00:20:00,080
Why don't we go peek through the window?

403
00:20:00,730 --> 00:20:02,790
It's all women inside. What are you trying to peek at?

404
00:20:02,990 --> 00:20:04,190
What are you thinking?

405
00:20:07,180 --> 00:20:09,030
I've pretended to be a woman for too long.

406
00:20:09,050 --> 00:20:10,870
I've forgotten that I'm not actually a woman.

407
00:20:11,030 --> 00:20:12,950
This is really becoming a problem now.

408
00:20:14,990 --> 00:20:16,230
They're really not coming out, huh?

409
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:20,640
Why don't we go for a walk on the street?

410
00:20:20,670 --> 00:20:21,510
Waiting here

411
00:20:21,550 --> 00:20:23,030
seems like a waste of time.

412
00:20:23,050 --> 00:20:23,910
Let's go.

413
00:20:33,760 --> 00:20:35,190
It's always like this every time we go out.

414
00:20:35,210 --> 00:20:36,710
Look, the wind has picked up.

415
00:20:36,820 --> 00:20:39,050
I told you to wear more, but you just wouldn't listen.

416
00:20:39,270 --> 00:20:40,500
I'm not cold.

417
00:20:40,550 --> 00:20:42,680
You must be cold. Look, you're shivering.

418
00:20:42,710 --> 00:20:43,760
You'll catch a cold again.

419
00:20:44,100 --> 00:20:45,500
I'm really not cold.

420
00:20:45,520 --> 00:20:46,590
I've noticed that you

421
00:20:46,620 --> 00:20:47,990
are becoming more and more disobedient.

422
00:20:48,020 --> 00:20:49,480
You weren't like this before.

423
00:20:49,620 --> 00:20:50,720
I used to be naive.

424
00:20:50,720 --> 00:20:51,830
I thought everything you said was right.

425
00:20:51,850 --> 00:20:53,460
Now I won't be fooled by you anymore.

426
00:20:53,800 --> 00:20:54,600
Fooled?

427
00:20:54,650 --> 00:20:55,920
Do I have any reason to fool you?

428
00:20:55,950 --> 00:20:57,080
You're always telling me what to do,

429
00:20:57,090 --> 00:20:58,450
but you can't even do it yourself.

430
00:20:58,930 --> 00:21:00,340
I'm just trying to do what's best for you.

431
00:21:00,670 --> 00:21:01,990
If you weren't my daughter,

432
00:21:02,010 --> 00:21:03,290
I wouldn't bother caring about you at all.

433
00:21:03,310 --> 00:21:04,710
Always meddling in everything.

434
00:21:04,780 --> 00:21:06,630
Is it really for the daughter's good?

435
00:21:07,810 --> 00:21:09,310
I don't think so.

436
00:21:09,510 --> 00:21:12,040
If everything has to be controlled so strictly,

437
00:21:12,400 --> 00:21:13,470
then I might

438
00:21:13,620 --> 00:21:14,940
not like this mother as much anymore.

439
00:21:14,960 --> 00:21:15,640
You're so lazy.

440
00:21:15,670 --> 00:21:17,900
Your in-laws will despise you when you get married.

441
00:21:18,040 --> 00:21:20,170
Then why aren't you despised by your in-laws?

442
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:22,260
That's because your grandmother passed away early.

443
00:21:22,640 --> 00:21:24,380
I was just lucky, okay?

444
00:21:24,450 --> 00:21:26,410
Then I'll marry a man without a mother.

445
00:21:26,510 --> 00:21:27,980
But you'll still have a father-in-law.

446
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:29,500
He'll despise you too.

447
00:21:29,520 --> 00:21:31,570
Then I'll marry a man without parents.

448
00:21:31,590 --> 00:21:32,920
You're really driving me crazy.

449
00:21:32,950 --> 00:21:35,720
A man without parents must be from a poor family.

450
00:21:35,750 --> 00:21:37,110
He won't even be able to afford the bride price.

451
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:39,380
I actually fit that condition quite well.

452
00:21:42,240 --> 00:21:43,730
That being said,

453
00:21:44,430 --> 00:21:45,640
actually,

454
00:21:45,850 --> 00:21:47,640
I'm quite envious of this daughter.

455
00:21:48,390 --> 00:21:49,850
I thought you didn't like it?

456
00:21:50,240 --> 00:21:53,380
I just don't like this form of it.

457
00:21:54,030 --> 00:21:55,100
But

458
00:21:56,290 --> 00:21:59,290
I've never had anyone be so strict with me since I was little.

459
00:21:59,950 --> 00:22:02,210
No one has ever disciplined me so seriously.

460
00:22:03,600 --> 00:22:06,060
I think being disciplined like this

461
00:22:06,410 --> 00:22:08,210
might be another kind of happiness.

462
00:22:10,840 --> 00:22:12,410
They've been following them.

463
00:22:12,470 --> 00:22:14,510
Could there be something wrong with this mother and daughter?

464
00:22:14,770 --> 00:22:15,990
There must be something wrong with them.

465
00:22:16,030 --> 00:22:18,130
Otherwise, why would they observe so carefully?

466
00:22:18,210 --> 00:22:20,080
Is Wang using this kind of people now?

467
00:22:20,180 --> 00:22:21,530
This is too covert.

468
00:22:21,560 --> 00:22:23,410
No wonder we hadn't found any clues.

469
00:22:23,680 --> 00:22:25,850
His strategies are almost as good as our Mingyi Manor's.

470
00:22:27,210 --> 00:22:28,920
Could they be the General's subordinates?

471
00:22:28,960 --> 00:22:31,790
Why would Vegetable follow the General's people?

472
00:22:32,950 --> 00:22:33,800
That's true.

473
00:22:33,830 --> 00:22:35,210
They're on the same side now.

474
00:22:35,950 --> 00:22:37,360
I never thought that

475
00:22:37,390 --> 00:22:39,510
we'd be on the same side as our old enemies some day.

476
00:22:39,540 --> 00:22:41,100
The world is too complicated.

477
00:22:41,640 --> 00:22:43,430
My brain can't keep up.

478
00:22:43,720 --> 00:22:44,530
Go away.

479
00:22:45,060 --> 00:22:45,830
Don't follow me.

480
00:22:45,850 --> 00:22:46,510
Mom.

481
00:22:46,550 --> 00:22:47,270
Seriously.

482
00:22:47,270 --> 00:22:48,270
So fierce.

483
00:22:50,640 --> 00:22:52,950
Will Chunlan and Qiu Ju misunderstand?

484
00:22:53,070 --> 00:22:55,280
They might think there's something wrong with that mother and daughter.

485
00:22:56,100 --> 00:22:57,390
We'll explain to them later.

486
00:22:58,000 --> 00:22:59,240
How should we explain?

487
00:22:59,420 --> 00:23:01,590
Telling them I'm learning how to be a mother?

488
00:23:06,750 --> 00:23:08,590
Don't pull me like that.

489
00:23:08,620 --> 00:23:09,370
Mom.

490
00:23:09,400 --> 00:23:09,880
Don't.

491
00:23:09,910 --> 00:23:11,110
Go follow someone else.

492
00:23:11,130 --> 00:23:11,470
Mom.

493
00:23:11,470 --> 00:23:12,360
Don't pull me.

494
00:23:12,960 --> 00:23:13,970
Mom.

495
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:14,790
You're so annoying.

496
00:23:15,110 --> 00:23:16,230
You never listen to what I say.

497
00:23:20,760 --> 00:23:22,080
It's so ugly.

498
00:23:22,150 --> 00:23:23,770
I don't want to wear this color.

499
00:23:23,790 --> 00:23:26,270
Only old ladies wear such dark clothes.

500
00:23:26,300 --> 00:23:27,640
I want this pink one.

501
00:23:27,720 --> 00:23:29,210
You're just a little kid.

502
00:23:29,260 --> 00:23:30,370
What do you know?

503
00:23:30,540 --> 00:23:31,570
You're so fat.

504
00:23:31,680 --> 00:23:32,990
You'll look like a pig in pink.

505
00:23:32,990 --> 00:23:34,160
Why don't we change a few more targets?

506
00:23:34,210 --> 00:23:34,840
This one it is.

507
00:23:34,840 --> 00:23:36,310
-This way, they should be able to figure it out.
-You always provoke me.

508
00:23:36,310 --> 00:23:37,310
There are no pink pigs, okay?

509
00:23:37,350 --> 00:23:38,590
There will be one when you wear it.

510
00:23:38,970 --> 00:23:40,830
You really are my own mother.

511
00:23:41,490 --> 00:23:43,370
Can't you say something nice?

512
00:23:44,900 --> 00:23:46,460
If I weren't your own mother,

513
00:23:47,150 --> 00:23:49,330
would I take you to buy fabric for new clothes?

514
00:23:49,360 --> 00:23:50,810
Try finding a stepmother.

515
00:23:51,290 --> 00:23:53,690
Maybe a stepmother would be better than you.

516
00:23:55,150 --> 00:23:56,640
You ungrateful child.

517
00:23:57,050 --> 00:23:58,980
How did I give birth to a daughter like you?

518
00:23:59,210 --> 00:24:00,410
What a sin I've committed.

519
00:24:00,560 --> 00:24:02,290
It's not like I asked you to give birth to me.

520
00:24:02,310 --> 00:24:03,790
You could have not given birth to me, right?

521
00:24:03,830 --> 00:24:04,910
You're driving me crazy.

522
00:24:05,520 --> 00:24:07,070
If I had known, I would have thrown you away.

523
00:24:07,160 --> 00:24:08,690
Even an adopted daughter would be better than you.

524
00:24:08,710 --> 00:24:10,560
If you're so capable, throw me away now.

525
00:24:10,580 --> 00:24:11,780
-Throw me! Throw me!
-You...

526
00:24:12,490 --> 00:24:14,100
You'll understand when you become a mother.

527
00:24:14,480 --> 00:24:15,840
What an unfilial daughter.

528
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:17,490
When I become a mother,

529
00:24:17,680 --> 00:24:19,290
if I have a daughter like you,

530
00:24:19,320 --> 00:24:20,290
I'll definitely throw her away.

531
00:24:20,310 --> 00:24:20,820
You!

532
00:24:20,860 --> 00:24:21,820
Stop right there!

533
00:24:22,480 --> 00:24:23,630
I said stop!

534
00:24:25,740 --> 00:24:28,230
What kind of fabric would you like to buy this time?

535
00:24:29,170 --> 00:24:30,260
Well, this time,

536
00:24:30,600 --> 00:24:33,460
I'd like to buy some fabric that you don't have at your stall.

537
00:24:33,590 --> 00:24:34,840
Can you sell it to me?

538
00:24:36,520 --> 00:24:37,600
Fabric that we don't have...

539
00:24:41,020 --> 00:24:42,290
You're getting more and more mischievous.

540
00:24:42,310 --> 00:24:44,020
You scared the stall owner silly.

541
00:24:44,850 --> 00:24:47,660
That's what he gets for acting like a petty swindler before.

542
00:24:49,920 --> 00:24:52,260
Indeed, women are not to be trifled with.

543
00:24:56,170 --> 00:24:57,360
You know,

544
00:24:57,380 --> 00:24:58,590
you've said the same thing to me before.

545
00:24:58,760 --> 00:25:00,190
But now,

546
00:25:00,290 --> 00:25:02,480
I finally understand what you meant.

547
00:25:03,100 --> 00:25:03,820
However,

548
00:25:03,930 --> 00:25:05,610
why are all the mother-daughter pairs we've observed

549
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:06,630
so disharmonious?

550
00:25:06,770 --> 00:25:08,790
Are all mother-daughter relationships like this?

551
00:25:09,160 --> 00:25:10,620
I guess most of them are like this.

552
00:25:10,660 --> 00:25:12,000
They all quarrel a lot.

553
00:25:12,230 --> 00:25:13,620
I don't think there are many

554
00:25:13,850 --> 00:25:15,790
mother-daughter relationships

555
00:25:15,830 --> 00:25:16,910
that are very harmonious and peaceful.

